  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation to combat money laundering has evolved significantly over the past few decades:\n\n1. Early Stages\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970, US)\n- First international anti-money laundering guidelines\n- Limited scope and enforcement\n\n2. Major Milestones\n- FATF establishment (1989)\n- International money laundering prevention standards\n- Increased global cooperation\n- Enhanced reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legislative Developments\n- Patriot Act (2001)\n- Expanded financial institution reporting obligations\n- Increased penalties for non-compliance\n- Enhanced international information sharing\n\n4. Modern Approaches\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Enhanced digital transaction monitoring\n- Machine learning and AI-driven detection\n- Stricter Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n5. Recent Trends\n- Beneficial ownership transparency\n- Enhanced whistleblower protections\n- Cross-border regulatory collaboration\n- More comprehensive risk-based approaches\n\n6. Technological Integration\n- Real-time transaction monitoring\n- Advanced data analytics\n- Automated suspicious activity detection\n- Blockchain tracking mechanisms\n\n7. Global Regulatory Frameworks\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- EU Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Consistent international standards\n- Coordinated enforcement strategies\n\nThe legislative landscape continues to evolve rapidly.",
